If you run it without parameters, it should give you an error message indicating the format it&#039;s expecting:
&lt;pre lang=&quot;text&quot;&gt; E:\programming\PhantomExperiments\AdvancedSmokeTest [master]&gt; phantomjs.exe test.js Must pass these 3 args when running script: -u [username] -p [password] -n [displayed user&#039;s name] &lt;/pre&gt;
So your example would look like this: &lt;pre lang=&quot;text&quot;&gt; E:\programming\PhantomExperiments\AdvancedSmokeTest [master]&gt; phantomjs.exe test.js -u Testuser1 -p Testuser1 -n Testuser [OUT] [Step 1 ] Load the site, we won&#039;t be logged in [---] [goToUrl ] http://lessthandot.com/ [---] [onUrlChanged ] Going to http://lessthandot.com/ ... &lt;/pre&gt;
